Program: The Reith Lectures
Title: A Community of Communities
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00gxthb
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 19 Dec 1990
In his sixth and final Reith Lecture, Dr. Jonathan Sacks, Chief Rabbi of the United Hebrew Congregations of the Commonwealth, explains why faith will survive. Dr. Jonathan Sacks explores in his lecture entitled 'A Community of Communities' the bond of religion. He explains that although the numbers of religious believers seems to be dwindling, religion will never totally fade away. He believes that the values it provides communities are still needed by the individual and the nation. Show less